$PAR
(i) What are the critical numbers of \(f\)?$BR
Critical numbers: \(x =\)\{ans_rule(30)\}
$PAR
(ii) Where is \(f\) increasing? $BR
\(f\) is increasing on \{ans_rule(30)\} \{AnswerFormatHelp("Intervals")\}
$PAR
(iii) Where is \(f\) decreasing? $BR
\(f\) is decreasing on \{ans_rule(30)\} \{AnswerFormatHelp("Intervals")\}
$PAR
(iv) At which \(x\) does \(f\) achieve its local maxima? $BR
\(f\) achieves local maxima at \(x = \) \{ans_rule(30)\}
$PAR
(v) At which \(x\) does \(f\) achieve its local minima? $BR
\(f\) achieves local minima at \(x = \) \{ans_rule(30)\}
$PAR
(vi) Where is \(f\) concave up? $BR
\(f\) is concave up on \{ans_rule(30)\} \{AnswerFormatHelp("Intervals")\}
$PAR
(vii) Where is \(f\) concave down? $BR
\(f\) is concave down on \{ans_rule(30)\} \{AnswerFormatHelp("Intervals")\}
